<h2>1. About this manual</h2>
<p>This manual is your reference document for owning and operating your solar system. It is issued at the time of system handover by <span class="fill">[INSTALLER COMPANY NAME]</span> in accordance with Clean Energy Council (CEC) Code of Conduct and AS/NZS 5033 requirements.</p>
<p>Keep this manual in a safe place &mdash; you will need it for insurance claims, warranty claims, when selling your house, when the network distributor visits, and when any future contractor works on your system. A digital copy is also available in your customer portal under <strong>Documents</strong>.</p>
<div class="warning">If your system is grid-connected, you should also have received the companion document <strong>"Grid-Connect Solar Owner's Manual"</strong> covering your network connection, anti-islanding behaviour, feed-in tariff and retailer obligations. If you did not receive this, contact your installer.</div>

<h2>2. Your system at a glance</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Field</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
<tr><td>Customer name</td><td><span class="fill">[CUSTOMER NAME]</span></td></tr>
<tr><td>Install address</td><td><span class="fill">[INSTALL ADDRESS]</span></td></tr>
<tr><td>System size (DC)</td><td><span class="fill">[X.X] kW</span></td></tr>
<tr><td>System size (AC, inverter rating)</td><td><span class="fill">[X.X] kW</span></td></tr>
<tr><td>Number of panels</td><td><span class="fill">[N]</span></td></tr>
<tr><td>Panel make &amp; model</td><td><span class="fill">[BRAND] [MODEL] [W per panel]</span></td></tr>
<tr><td>Inverter make &amp; model</td><td><span class="fill">[BRAND] [MODEL]</span></td></tr>
